  fhir:description [ fhir:v "SNOMED CT concepts that may indicate a risk to healthcare personnel emanating from the patient.\nIncludes selected children of the Infectious disease hierarchy whose descendants are person-to-person transmissible — viral, bacterial, sexually transmitted, respiratory, healthcare-associated and parasitic disease — plus an aggressive behavior finding.\nBranches that do not pose a meaningful staff-transmission risk (anatomical-location infections, post-procedural / device-associated infections, sepsis variants, congenital and perinatal infections, plant / Microspora / Oomycota / fish infections, and the like) are excluded."] ; # 
